cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the Annotation Graph Toolkit (AGTK) which is a collection of software for linguistic annotation tools. The paper focuses on collaborative annotation and how it can be supported with tools built using AGTK and its database interface. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the relational database schema and API, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DB (Databases). The high-level query language for annotation graphs and optimizations suggest that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Learning). Finally, the topic of linguistic annotation could also suggest that it could belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
